CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, national edition, October 16, 1943, pg. 11, reads: "Nation's Outstanding Women Gather For Elaborate Christening!  Pictured here is a group of the innumerable widely-known women, leaders in civic and social affairs from all sections of the country, who travelled thousands of miles to see Mrs. Robert L. Vann christen the Liberty Ship 'Robert L. Vann' at Portland, Maine. Fashionably attired, they stand in shipyard waiting the thrilling moment when the bottle is broken and the magic words are pronounced. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of women, front row from left: Tolki Schalk (Johnson), two unknown women, Mable Page Johnson, Daisy Lampkin, Jessie Vann, Blanche Morris, Harriet Lewis looking back, two unknown women, Eve Lynn Reynolds, and four unknown women, standing in front of stone building for christening ceremony of SS Robert L. Vann, Portland, Maine
